Designer, quilter, textile historian and author, Darlene Zimmerman has been an integral part of the quilting industry for twelve years. Throughout this time Darlene has authored eight quilting books; still in print are Quilts to Come Home To, Quick Quilted Miniatures, Granny Quilts, Granny Quilt Decor, and Fat Quarter Small Quilts. In September her newest book, The Quilter's Edge, will be released. She has appeared in countless quilting magazines, the T.V. show &quot;Sew Creative,&quot; and continues to lecture and teach nationally for shops, guilds and symposiums.
